	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64551803"><p>My understanding of Dyson spheres is that they're habitats (yielding a LOT of room) built by civilizations that don't have star travel.  The conflict is, as I remember, that it takes so much matter and energy to build them that every planetary system within light-years would need to be scoured for building materials.  So on the one hand, a Dyson sphere would yield the living area of thousands of planets, which would eliminate the need for a stellar drive (at least, for a very long time) but on the other han<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

